# Using Event Sourcing on AWS (Backend)

Use this rule when working on **backend** code: Lambda handlers, capability `domain/` packages, or `cfb-event-sourcing`.

For entity design and action patterns, see `planning-event-sourcing-aggregate.mdc`.
For test examples, see `testing-event-sourced-aggregates.mdc`.

## The split (one sentence)

**Core defines streams and `streamId`; AWS implements them; capability domain uses them; handlers wire AWS to domain.**

---

## Three layers of responsibility

| Layer | Package | Owns |
|-------|---------|------|
| Event-sourcing domain | `cfb-event-sourcing-core` | `streamId`, `ReadOnlyStream`, `AppendEnabledStream` port shapes: `(streamId) => { do }` |
| Event-sourcing AWS | `cfb-event-sourcing-aws` | `createReadOnlyStream(streamOptions)`, `createAppendEnabledStream(streamOptions)`, RDS, EventBridge |
| Capability | `domain/` + `aws-handlers/` | Business entities/actions; Lambda HTTP adapters |

**`streamOptions` is AWS-only.** Handler passes it to `create*Stream`. Domain never sees it.

**`streamId` is a core/domain concept.** Capability action passes it into the port: `appendStream(streamId).do(...)`.

---

## Folder map

### Shared framework (`cfb-event-sourcing/`)

```
cfb-event-sourcing/
├── core/       @rinkkasatiainen/cfb-event-sourcing-core
│   └── src/
│       ├── stream-ports.js   ← ReadOnlyStream, AppendEnabledStream (domain concepts)
│       ├── event.js
│       └── apply-events.js
├── aws/        @rinkkasatiainen/cfb-event-sourcing-aws
│   └── src/
│       ├── streams.js        ← createReadOnlyStream(streamOptions), createAppendEnabledStream(streamOptions)
│       ├── event-store.js
│       └── event-bus.js
└── testing/    @rinkkasatiainen/cfb-event-sourcing-testing
```

### Your capability (e.g. `cfb-npm-template/`)

```
cfb-your-capability/
├── domain/           @rinkkasatiainen/cfb-your-capability-domain
│   └── src/
│       ├── entities/
│       └── actions/          ← appendStream(streamId).do(...)
│
└── aws-handlers/     @rinkkasatiainen/cfb-your-capability-aws-handlers
    └── src/
        └── handlers/         ← create*Stream(streamOptions), pass port to action
```

